CC   -!- FUNCTION: Alpha-glucuronidase involved in the hydrolysis of xylan,
CC       a major structural heterogeneous polysaccharide found in plant
CC       biomass representing the second most abundant polysaccharide in
CC       the biosphere, after cellulose. Releases 4-O-methylglucuronic acid
CC       from xylan. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:16844780}.
CC   -!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: An alpha-D-glucuronoside + H(2)O = an alcohol
CC       + D-glucuronate.
CC   -!- BIOPHYSICOCHEMICAL PROPERTIES:
CC       pH dependence:
CC         Optimum pH is 4.0. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:16844780};
CC       Temperature dependence:
CC         Optimum temperature is 30 degrees Celsius.
CC         {ECO:0000269|PubMed:16844780};
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000250}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the glycosyl hydrolase 67 family.
CC       {ECO:0000305}.

CC   -!- FUNCTION: Alpha-glucuronidase involved in the hydrolysis of xylan,
CC       a major structural heterogeneous polysaccharide found in plant
CC       biomass representing the second most abundant polysaccharide in
CC       the biosphere, after cellulose. Releases 4-O-methylglucuronic acid
CC       from xylan. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:10779688,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:9440512}.

CC       Temperature dependence:

CC         {ECO:0000269|PubMed:9440512};
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted.
CC   -!- INDUCTION: By xylan and xylose but not by glucuronic acid.

RP   NUCLEOTIDE SEQUENCE [GENOMIC DNA], AND INDUCTION.
RC   STRAIN=ATCC 9029 / NRRL 3 / CBS 120.49 / DSM 2466 / N400;
RX   PubMed=12242504; DOI=10.1007/s00438-002-0729-7;
RA   de Vries R.P., van de Vondervoort P.J.I., Hendriks L., van de Belt M.,

CC   -!- FUNCTION: Alpha-glucuronidase involved in the hydrolysis of xylan,
CC       a major structural heterogeneous polysaccharide found in plant
CC       biomass representing the second most abundant polysaccharide in
CC       the biosphere, after cellulose. Releases 4-O-methylglucuronic acid
CC       from xylan (By similarity). {ECO:0000250}.
CC   -!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: An alpha-D-glucuronoside + H(2)O = an alcohol
CC       + D-glucuronate.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000250}.
CC   -!- INDUCTION: Expressed in the presence of D-xylose and L-arabinose
CC       and at very low level in the presence of D-glucuronic acid.
CC       Expression is under the control of the xylanolytic transcriptional
CC       activator xlnR and the carbon catabolite repressor creA.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:12242504}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the glycosyl hydrolase 67 family.
CC       {ECO:0000305}.

CC   -!- FUNCTION: Alpha-glucuronidase involved in the hydrolysis of xylan,

CC       biomass representing the second most abundant polysaccharide in

CC       from xylan. {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.

CC   -!- FUNCTION: Transcriptional activator of the xylanolytic system.
CC       Involved in the regulation of extracellular cellulolytic and
CC       xylanolytic genes and in the regulation of the intracellular
CC       activities of D-xylose catabolic genes in the pentose catabolic
CC       pathway (PCP) in response to the presence of D-xylose. Binds to
CC       the DNA sequence 5'-GGNTAAA-3'. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:10508057,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:10760176, ECO:0000269|PubMed:11916668,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:12242504, ECO:0000269|PubMed:17951513,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:18332432, ECO:0000269|PubMed:21484208,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:21892241, ECO:0000269|PubMed:9758775,
CC       ECO:0000269|Ref.8}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Nucleus.
CC   -!- INDUCTION: Expressed in presence of xylose.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18332432}.
CC   -!- DISRUPTION PHENOTYPE: Reduces growth on birchwod xylan, while
CC       growth is unaffected on D-xylose, xylitol and other carbon sources
CC       like D-glucose, L-arabinose or L-arabitol.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:21892241, ECO:0000269|Ref.8}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the xlnR/xlr1 family. {ECO:0000305}.

CC   -!- FUNCTION: Alpha-glucuronidase involved in the hydrolysis of xylan,
CC       a major structural heterogeneous polysaccharide found in plant
CC       biomass representing the second most abundant polysaccharide in
CC       the biosphere, after cellulose. Releases 4-O-methylglucuronic acid
CC       from xylan. {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.
CC   -!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: An alpha-D-glucuronoside + H(2)O = an alcohol
CC       + D-glucuronate. {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the glycosyl hydrolase 67 family.

CC   -!- FUNCTION: Alpha-glucuronidase involved in the hydrolysis of xylan,
CC       a major structural heterogeneous polysaccharide found in plant
CC       biomass representing the second most abundant polysaccharide in
CC       the biosphere, after cellulose. Releases 4-O-methylglucuronic acid
CC       from xylan. {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.
CC   -!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: An alpha-D-glucuronoside + H(2)O = an alcohol
CC       + D-glucuronate. {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000256|RuleBase:RU361198}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the glycosyl hydrolase 67 family.
